reviews.review_text:
Nice Matrix ! Nice sounding Matrix of a solid show!
I'll Admit I am a sound snob when it comes to looking for shows to download, of course it has to be a great show musically first then I look for the best sounding version to download and it is a shame that a lot of the 80's cassette masters have what I feel is quite a lot of hiss - but folks like Mr. Tobin and others are doing a great job making matrix's of a lot of these shows and it seems that the audience part of the matrix cancels out most of the hiss - call me crazy but that is how it seems , like noise canceling and because of this I have added this show and many more to my collection recently - my 1st show was 10-30-70 at Stony Brook (cost 2 dollars) and it is great that because of the work of all these people I can go back and listen to almost all the shows I have been to or desperately wished I was at - every show should have a matrix version.
lay me down. black peter!! good lay me down black peter, amen to all other comments
